'''Sarah Bouyain''' (born 1968) is a [[French people|French]]-[[Burkina Faso|Burkinab<U+00E9>]] writer and film director.

==Biography==
Bouyain was born in [[Reims]], [[Marne]], [[France]]. Her mother, who was French, and her father, who was half Burkinab<U+00E9> and half French, met in [[France]] while he was studying there.<ref name=lce2>{{cite web |url= http://lachambredechos.com/bouyain2.html|title= Sarah Bouyain <U+2013> Entretien avec Jean-Louis Ughetto|accessdate=2007-06-16 |date=October 2002|language=French|work= lachambredechos.com|publisher=La chambre d<U+2019><U+00E9>chos |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070928060025/http://lachambredechos.com/bouyain2.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-28}}</ref>

Having originally studied [[mathematics]], Bouyain later shifted her attention to [[cinematography]],<ref name=lce>{{cite web |url= http://lachambredechos.com/bouyain.html|title=M<U+00E9>tisse fa<U+00E7>on, recueil de nouvelles de Sarah Bouyain|accessdate=2007-06-16 |language=French|work= lachambredechos.com|publisher=La chambre d<U+2019><U+00E9>chos |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070928060032/http://lachambredechos.com/bouyain.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-28}}</ref> studying at the Louis Lumi<U+00E8>re School of Cinematography. She went on to work as a camerawomen for several films, and eventually directed several of her own.<ref name=tv5>{{cite web |url= http://www.tv5.org/TV5Site/cinema/afriq_fiche.php?id_realisateur=2314&position=20&search=realisateur&recherche=&pays=&categorie=&genre=&annee=&page=1&action=ok&lettre=b |title=Sarah BOUYAIN |accessdate=2007-06-16 |language=French|work= Les cin<U+00E9>mas d'Afrique|publisher=[[TV5MONDE]]}}</ref>

She wrote her book ''Metisse fa<U+00E7>on'' after researching her [[Africa]]n heritage in Burkina Faso. She learned of the history of [[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]] (as Burkina Faso was known in [[Colonialism|colonial]] times) and of children who were born to African women and French soldiers only to be forced to leave their mothers to live in orphanages. The characters in ''Metisse fa<U+00E7>on'' are based on these children.<ref>{{Cite news
  | last =Aron
  | first =Ariane
  | title =M<U+00E9>tisse Fa<U+00E7>on-Un recueil de nouvelles de Sarah Bouyain 
  | newspaper =Amina
  | volume =398
  | pages =66
  | date =June 2003
  | accessdate=2007-06-11
  | url =http://aflit.arts.uwa.edu.au/AMINAbouyain.html
  | postscript =<!--None--> }} {{fr icon}}</ref>

Bouyain has also written articles, mainly on the theme of mixed-race and exile, for [[Africultures]], ''[[Presence Africaine]]'' and [[CODESRIA]].<ref>[http://africanwomenincinema.blogspot.co.uk/2011/02/sarah-bouyain-notre-etrangerethe-place.html "Sarah Bouyain: Notre <U+00E9>trang<U+00E8>re/The Place in Between", African Women in Cinema, 28 February 2011.]</ref>

Her first feature-length film is ''Notre <U+00C9>trang<U+00E8>re'' ("The Place In Between"; 2010), which ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' called " A nicely observed docudrama about a biracial young French woman who goes back to her roots."<ref>[http://www1.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/film-reviews/the-place-in-between-film-review-1004117245.story  Michael Rechtshaffen, "The Place in Between -- Film Review", ''The Hollywood Reporter'', September 28, 2010.]</ref> It premiered at the 2010 Toronto International Film Festival.

==Works==

===Films===
*''Niararaye'' (1997)
*''Les enfants du Blanc'' (documentary; 2000)
*''[[The Place in Between]]'' (2010)

===Books===
*''M<U+00E9>tisse fa<U+00E7>on'' (short stories; 2003)

